  alternative (monkey-patching the allowlist) weakens a security
  gate for test convenience.

## Traps carried over from W22.a

- `tracker.log_figure` is `async def` on real `ExperimentRun` but the
  callback uses `asyncio.run(coro)` ‚Äî this RAISES `RuntimeError:
  asyncio.run() cannot be called from a running event loop` if
  Lightning is driven from inside an async parent. The defensive
  `result.close()` branch handles it but SILENTLY DROPS the
  emission. A real-tracker Tier-2 needs an event-loop-aware bridge
  (e.g., `asyncio.run_coroutine_threadsafe` to a dedicated worker
  loop). Out of scope for W22.b; flag if W22.c re-opens it.
- `MLEngine` has no `close()` method. Broader engine-suite runs
  segfault during aiosqlite teardown when many tests run together;
  use per-file invocation or the `managed_engines` factory fixture.
- `DLDiagnostics.plot_*()` methods don't return `None` on empty
  logs ‚Äî they return minimal plotly Figures. Tests that only assert
  `.calls` length can pass without detecting "emitted but empty";
  assert `figure_type == "Figure"` if substance matters.

